      "WE NOW HAVE A MOMENTUM TO DEAL WITH THIS PROBLEM IN THE REGION, BUT IT MUST BE LINKED TO A POLITICAL SETTLEMENT OF THE ARAB-ISRAELI PROBLEM. WE WON'T GET ANYWHERE ON NON-IRAQ SPECIFIC ARMS CONTROL WITHOUT WORKING ON THIS POLITICAL ISSUE. 18. UNDER SECRETARY KIMMITT SAID THAT WE SEE THE INTERRELATIONSHIP AMONG POLITICAL, ECONOMIC AND SECURITY ISSUES. BUT WE WON'T IMPROV",
      "UESTION, ALTHOUGH THE CONGRESS HAS ALREADY TRIED TO LIMIT COULD CONVENTIONAL WEAPONS. KASEL ASKED WHETHER THIS INCLUDED ISRAELI NUCLEAR CAPABILITY. RICHARD HAASS SAID THAT OUR PROVE FIRST OBJECTIVE WAS TO PREVENT THINGS GOING TO IRAQ AND FUTILE PREVENT OTHERS FROM GETTING NUCLEAR CAPABILITIES. ISRAEL IS DIFFERENT IN TWO WAYS: FIRST, ISRAEL ALREADY HAS A AND NUCLEAR"
